<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>6th Grade Math Interactive YAG</title>
    <style>
        /* CSS: Reskinned to a Dark Mode / Tech Aesthetic */
        body {
            font-family: 'Courier New', Courier, monospace;
            background-color: #121212; /* Dark/Black Background */
            margin: 0;
            padding: 20px;
            color: #e0e0e0; /* Light text for readability */
        }
        header {
            text-align: center;
            background-color: #1a1a1a;
            color: #00ff66; /* Vibrant Neon Green */
            padding: 20px;
            border-radius: 8px;
            border: 1px solid #333;
            box-shadow: 0 4px 10px rgba(0, 255, 102, 0.1);
        }
        h1 {
            margin: 0;
            font-size: 28px;
            letter-spacing: 1px;
        }
        header p {
            margin: 5px 0 0 0;
            color: #ffcc00; /* Yellow Subtitle */
            opacity: 0.9;
        }
        .container {
            max-width: 1000px;
            margin: 20px auto;
        }
        .filter-section {
            background: #1a1a1a;
            padding: 15px;
            border-radius: 8px;
            margin-bottom: 25px;
            text-align: center;
            border: 1px solid #00ff66; /* Green Border */
        }
        label {
            font-size: 16px;
            color: #ffcc00; /* Yellow Text */
        }
        select {
            padding: 10px 15px;
            font-size: 16px;
            border-radius: 5px;
            border: 1px solid #00ff66;
            background-color: #121212;
            color: #00ff66;
            cursor: pointer;
            outline: none;
            font-family: inherit;
        }
        select:focus {
            box-shadow: 0 0 8px rgba(0, 255, 102, 0.5);
        }
        .calendar-card {
            background: #1e1e1e; /* Dark Gray Cards */
            padding: 20px;
            margin-bottom: 15px;
            border-radius: 8px;
            box-shadow: 0 2px 5px rgba(0,0,0,0.5);
            border-left: 6px solid #00ff66; /* Neon Green Left Border */
            transition: transform 0.2s;
        }
        .calendar-card:hover {
            transform: translateY(-2px);
            box-shadow: 0 4px 12px rgba(0, 255, 102, 0.15);
        }
        .calendar-card h3 {
            margin-top: 0;
            color: #00ff66; /* Neon Green Heading */
            border-bottom: 1px solid #333;
            padding-bottom: 8px;
        }
        .date-row {
            margin: 10px 0;
            line-height: 1.5;
        }
        .date-badge {
            display: inline-block;
            background-color: #333;
            color: #00ff66; /* Green Text on Dark Badge */
            border: 1px solid #00ff66;
            padding: 3px 8px;
            border-radius: 4px;
            font-weight: bold;
            font-size: 13px;
            margin-right: 10px;
        }
        .honors-badge {
            display: inline-block;
            background-color: #00ff66;
            color: #121212; /* Inverted for Honors emphasis */
            padding: 3px 8px;
            border-radius: 4px;
            font-weight: bold;
            font-size: 13px;
            margin-right: 10px;
        }
        .assessment-note {
            background-color: #2a2510; /* Dark Yellow Tint */
            border: 1px dashed #ffcc00; /* Yellow Dash */
            color: #ffcc00; /* Alert Yellow Text */
            padding: 10px;
            border-radius: 5px;
            margin-top: 10px;
            font-weight: bold;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

    <header>
        <h1>6th Grade Math Pacing & YAG</h1>
        <p>[ System Status: Accelerated 7th Honors Track Connected ]</p>
    </header>

    <div class="container">
        
        <div class="filter-section">
            <label for="topicFilter"><strong>Execute Query (Filter):</strong> </label>
            <select id="topicFilter" onchange="filterCalendar()">
                <option value="all">Show Full Year Calendar</option>
                <option value="distributive">Distributive Property (Sept)</option>
                <option value="composite">Composite Area (6th Base & 7th Honors Extension)</option>
                <option value="integers">Operating with Integers (Feb)</option>
                <option value="representations">Multiple Representations (March)</option>
            </select>
        </div>

        <div id="calendarDisplay">

            <div class="calendar-card" data-topic="distributive">
                <h3>September 2026: Expression Fundamentals</h3>
                <div class="date-row">
                    <span class="date-badge">Sept 21</span> 
                    <strong>Station Day:</strong> MATHia CB — Exploring the distributive property with numeric expressions.
                </div>
                <div class="date-row">
                    <span class="date-badge">Sept 22</span> 
                    <strong>Mastery Lesson:</strong> Prime Factorization & Using the Distributive Property with Numeric Expressions.
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="calendar-card" data-topic="composite">
                <h3>October 2026: Base Geometry (Decomposing Polygons)</h3>
                <div class="date-row">
                    <span class="date-badge">Oct 13</span> 
                    <strong>Module 1 Topic 4 Lesson 3:</strong> Activities 1 & 2 + Talk the Talk (Decomposing irregular polygons into rectangles and triangles).
                </div>
                <div class="date-row">
                    <span class="date-badge">Oct 19 - 21</span> 
                    <strong>Module 1 Topic 4 Lesson 4:</strong> Multi-day sequence focusing heavily on composite area applications (Activities 1 through 6).
                </div>
                <div class="assessment-note">
                    SYSTEM ALERT: Upcoming Milestone - CBA #2 (Shapes, Solids, & Decimals Blueprint)
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="calendar-card" data-topic="composite">
                <h3>January 2027: 7th Grade Honors Accelerated Geometry Extension</h3>
                <div class="date-row">
                    <span class="honors-badge">Jan 5 - 6</span> 
                    <strong>Module 5 Topic 1 Lesson 3 (TEKS 7.9C):</strong> Advanced Composite Area (Determining area of composite figures containing rectangles, triangles, and rounded edges/semicircles).
                </div>
                <div class="date-row">
                    <span class="honors-badge">Jan 11</span> 
                    <strong>Station Day Integration:</strong> MATHia software session explicitly locked to compound geometry modules.
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="calendar-card" data-topic="integers">
                <h3>February 2027: Operating with Integers</h3>
                <div class="date-row">
                    <span class="date-badge">Feb 6 - 25</span> 
                    <strong>Module 3 Topic 2:</strong> Integer operations, absolute values, products/quotients, and modeling rules on number lines.
                </div>
                <div class="assessment-note">
                    SYSTEM ALERT: End of Unit - CBA #5 (Operating with Integers Blueprint) on February 26.
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="calendar-card" data-topic="representations">
                <h3>March 2027: Graphing Quantitative Relationships</h3>
                <div class="date-row">
                    <span class="date-badge">Early March</span> 
                    <strong>Module 4 Topic 3 Lessons 1 & 2:</strong> Modeling scenarios with equations, identifying independent vs. dependent variables from tables/graphs.
                </div>
                <div class="date-row">
                    <span class="date-badge">Mid-March</span> 
                    <strong>Module 4 Topic 3 Lessons 3 - 5:</strong> Connecting verbal descriptions, algebraic rules, tables, and full coordinate plane graphs.
                </div>
                <div class="assessment-note">
                    SYSTEM ALERT: End of Unit - CBA #7 (Graphing Quantitative Relationships Blueprint).
                </div>
            </div>

        </div>
    </div>

    <script>
        /* JAVASCRIPT: Evaluates dropdown changes and hides/shows content dynamically */
        function filterCalendar() {
            var selectedValue = document.getElementById("topicFilter").value;
            var cards = document.getElementsByClassName("calendar-card");

            for (var i = 0; i < cards.length; i++) {
                if (selectedValue === "all") {
                    cards[i].style.display = "block";
                } else if (cards[i].getAttribute("data-topic") === selectedValue) {
                    cards[i].style.display = "block";
                } else {
                    cards[i].style.display = "none";
                }
            }
        }
    </script>
</body>
</html>
